OL,3,CFather of US school shooting suspect
OL,4,Ccharged with murder
OL,6,FProsecutors can hold parents
OL,7,Fresponsible for their children's
OL,8,Factions in school shootings, often
OL,9,Funder state laws.
OL,11,FA key reason for prosecution is if a
OL,12,Fparent fails to secure a firearm
OL,13,Fproperly, and their child uses it in a
OL,14,Fshooting, the parent may face charges
OL,15,Frelated to the crime.
OL,17,FIn April, Michigan parents Jennifer
OL,18,Fand James Crumbley were the first
OL,19,Fconvicted in a US mass school shooting.
